{"personas":[{"red_flags":["formula selects a compiler implementation at runtime","raw contract remains the canonical decision point","requirement checks duplicated across projections and drift"],"questions_text":"Does the design keep the active Gas City binary as the only compiler decision-maker rather than letting formulas select implementations?;Is requirement normalization implemented in one internal/formula path so callers never check raw contract strings?;Are formula-v2 constructs validated in internal/formula while CLI, orders, sling, API, and convergence consume typed results?","slug":"01-compiler-boundary-invariant","mandate":"active binary ownership;normalized requirements;internal formula authority;ZFC and layering","red_flags_text":"formula selects a compiler implementation at runtime;raw contract remains the canonical decision point;requirement checks duplicated across projections and drift","questions":["Does the design keep the active Gas City binary as the only compiler decision-maker rather than letting formulas select implementations?","Is requirement normalization implemented in one internal/formula path so callers never check raw contract strings?","Are formula-v2 constructs validated in internal/formula while CLI, orders, sling, API, and convergence consume typed results?"],"name":"Nadia Sorenson","wave":1},{"red_flags":["legacy formulas fail abruptly","conflicting declarations are silently accepted","deprecation scheduled by calendar rather than remaining-usage evidence"],"questions_text":"Do existing contract = graph.v2 formulas continue compiling through the migration window, including externally pinned packs?;Are conflicts between contract and requires detected deterministically with a hard validation error?;What measurable trigger and owner decide when the alias can be removed?","red_flags_text":"legacy formulas fail abruptly;conflicting declarations are silently accepted;deprecation scheduled by calendar rather than remaining-usage evidence","mandate":"contract alias;existing formulas;deprecation window;warning reach","questions":["Do existing contract = graph.v2 formulas continue compiling through the migration window, including externally pinned packs?","Are conflicts between contract and requires detected deterministically with a hard validation error?","What measurable trigger and owner decide when the alias can be removed?"],"name":"Elias Vega","wave":1,"slug":"02-contract-migration-guardian"},{"questions_text":"Does v0 reject unsupported expressions such as exact 2, >=2.1, empty strings, and malformed ranges unless explicitly allowed?;Are empty [requires] tables, unknown sibling keys, and unknown contract values covered in validation tests?;Do v2-only constructs fail when the compiler requirement is omitted, regardless of caller path?","red_flags":["unknown ranges accepted silently","v2-only fields compile without a requirement","tests are hand-written per case and miss matrix combinations"],"questions":["Does v0 reject unsupported expressions such as exact 2, >=2.1, empty strings, and malformed ranges unless explicitly allowed?","Are empty [requires] tables, unknown sibling keys, and unknown contract values covered in validation tests?","Do v2-only constructs fail when the compiler requirement is omitted, regardless of caller path?"],"red_flags_text":"unknown ranges accepted silently;v2-only fields compile without a requirement;tests are hand-written per case and miss matrix combinations","mandate":"requirement grammar;parser edge cases;v2 construct enforcement;test matrix","wave":1,"name":"Priya Zielinski","slug":"03-parser-validation-matrix"},{"questions_text":"When daemon.formula_v2 is false, do CLI exits, API responses, dashboard cards, and order events share the same actionable remedy?;Does the gate apply to normalized compiler requirements regardless of whether the source used requires or contract?;Are deprecation warnings emitted at a controlled cadence that will not flood poll-driven dispatch or CI logs?","red_flags":["disabled-capability errors look like parse failures","dashboard and CLI give contradictory remedies","deprecation warnings fire on every resolve cycle"],"wave":1,"name":"Marta Hidalgo","questions":["When daemon.formula_v2 is false, do CLI exits, API responses, dashboard cards, and order events share the same actionable remedy?","Does the gate apply to normalized compiler requirements regardless of whether the source used requires or contract?","Are deprecation warnings emitted at a controlled cadence that will not flood poll-driven dispatch or CI logs?"],"mandate":"daemon formula_v2 gate;actionable errors;API CLI order consistency;warning rate limiting","red_flags_text":"disabled-capability errors look like parse failures;dashboard and CLI give contradictory remedies;deprecation warnings fire on every resolve cycle","slug":"04-operator-diagnostics-gate"},{"red_flags":["old and new requirement checks coexist indefinitely","bd fallback ignores requires","in-flight molecules enter an undefined state when the daemon flag changes"],"questions_text":"Has every caller of declaresGraphV2Contract across sling, orders, dispatch, API, dashboard, and convergence moved to one shared helper?;Do bd-backed and native compiler paths interpret normalized requirements identically during the migration?;If formula_v2 changes while a v2-required wisp or molecule is in flight, is the compile/retry behavior defined?","slug":"05-caller-integration-inventory","name":"Yuki Patel","wave":2,"mandate":"caller rewrite;bd and native path alignment;in-flight molecule behavior;dead-code policy","red_flags_text":"old and new requirement checks coexist indefinitely;bd fallback ignores requires;in-flight molecules enter an undefined state when the daemon flag changes","questions":["Has every caller of declaresGraphV2Contract across sling, orders, dispatch, API, dashboard, and convergence moved to one shared helper?","Do bd-backed and native compiler paths interpret normalized requirements identically during the migration?","If formula_v2 changes while a v2-required wisp or molecule is in flight, is the compile/retry behavior defined?"]},{"slug":"06-rollout-sequencing-reviewer","wave":2,"name":"Lena Driscoll","questions":["Can each migration step land with main working, or does the plan require a flag day across parser, callers, and docs?","If caller replacement regresses dispatch, can that step be reverted without also reverting docs and built-in formulas?","Are built-in and example formulas updated in a release where older binaries still parse them, or is version lockstep required?"],"red_flags_text":"built-in formulas switch syntax before compatibility support ships;rollback requires a multi-step revert;migration window lacks a measurable exit criterion","mandate":"implementation order;rollback granularity;built-in pack compatibility;migration-window definition","questions_text":"Can each migration step land with main working, or does the plan require a flag day across parser, callers, and docs?;If caller replacement regresses dispatch, can that step be reverted without also reverting docs and built-in formulas?;Are built-in and example formulas updated in a release where older binaries still parse them, or is version lockstep required?","red_flags":["built-in formulas switch syntax before compatibility support ships","rollback requires a multi-step revert","migration window lacks a measurable exit criterion"]},{"questions_text":"Does the design clearly remove formula-level artifact semver while preserving pack semver, refs, and SHAs as the reproducibility boundary?;What happens for external packs pinned by SHA that copy current contract examples?;Is there a gc formula validate or lint path that tells pack authors exactly how to migrate stale snippets?","red_flags":["version becomes de facto formula semver","external pack authors only get a changelog note","layer winners cannot be tied back to pack revision"],"slug":"07-pack-versioning-ecosystem","wave":2,"name":"Saoirse Raman","questions":["Does the design clearly remove formula-level artifact semver while preserving pack semver, refs, and SHAs as the reproducibility boundary?","What happens for external packs pinned by SHA that copy current contract examples?","Is there a gc formula validate or lint path that tells pack authors exactly how to migrate stale snippets?"],"red_flags_text":"version becomes de facto formula semver;external pack authors only get a changelog note;layer winners cannot be tied back to pack revision","mandate":"pack revision boundary;external author workflow;pinning and reproducibility;lint surface"},{"questions_text":"Do docs/reference/formula.md, tutorials, architecture docs, and examples all teach requires as the canonical surface in the same change?;Is there one glossary-level distinction between capability, implementation, contract, schema, and pack revision?;Should the open questions about exact values, warning transport, and legacy version be resolved before shipping?","red_flags":["docs continue recommending version or contract after behavior changes","requires is overloaded with another pack concept without explanation","open questions remain live at merge with user-visible consequences"],"slug":"08-docs-dx-terminology","questions":["Do docs/reference/formula.md, tutorials, architecture docs, and examples all teach requires as the canonical surface in the same change?","Is there one glossary-level distinction between capability, implementation, contract, schema, and pack revision?","Should the open questions about exact values, warning transport, and legacy version be resolved before shipping?"],"red_flags_text":"docs continue recommending version or contract after behavior changes;requires is overloaded with another pack concept without explanation;open questions remain live at merge with user-visible consequences","mandate":"documentation consistency;TOML user experience;terminology clarity;open question closure","wave":3,"name":"Avery Brooks"},{"red_flags_text":"convergence silently drops [requires];v2 capability gate is bypassed by convergence;convergence and canonical formula validation continue to drift","mandate":"convergence validator;subsystem coupling;formula subset drift;daemon gate coverage","questions":["Does internal/convergence/formula.go preserve and validate [requires] instead of dropping it from the subset?","If a convergence formula needs v2 capability, does convergence respect daemon.formula_v2 through the same path as dispatch?","Does adding [requires] reduce top-level key sprawl or create another precedent for subsystem-specific formula subsets?"],"name":"Felix Berger","wave":3,"slug":"09-convergence-subset-reviewer","red_flags":["convergence silently drops [requires]","v2 capability gate is bypassed by convergence","convergence and canonical formula validation continue to drift"],"questions_text":"Does internal/convergence/formula.go preserve and validate [requires] instead of dropping it from the subset?;If a convergence formula needs v2 capability, does convergence respect daemon.formula_v2 through the same path as dispatch?;Does adding [requires] reduce top-level key sprawl or create another precedent for subsystem-specific formula subsets?"},{"questions_text":"Does the string grammar leave room for future compiler capability ranges without committing to full semver in v0?;Are omitted, >=1, and >=2 semantics defined tightly enough to avoid accidental divergence later?;Are unknown keys under [requires] rejected or reserved in a way that can support future axes such as tools, pack format, or runtime?","red_flags":["v0 grammar blocks future capability growth","omitted and >=1 diverge accidentally","unsupported requirement axes are silently ignored"],"questions":["Does the string grammar leave room for future compiler capability ranges without committing to full semver in v0?","Are omitted, >=1, and >=2 semantics defined tightly enough to avoid accidental divergence later?","Are unknown keys under [requires] rejected or reserved in a way that can support future axes such as tools, pack format, or runtime?"],"red_flags_text":"v0 grammar blocks future capability growth;omitted and >=1 diverge accidentally;unsupported requirement axes are silently ignored","mandate":"future capability ranges;reserved requirement axes;minimal abstraction;unknown key policy","wave":3,"name":"Ibrahim Park","slug":"10-future-capability-architect"}]}